(training-pair-supplements-4b-readme
  :version "2"
  :kind "training-corpus/readme"
  :id "training-pair-supplements-4b-readme"
  :title "Training-Pair Supplements 4B — README"
  :date "2026-07-13"
  :author "Lacuna Labs (Sakura authoring lane)"
  :doctrine (:publishable-prose :familiarity-not-knowledge :delicacy :kid-at-the-other-end :no-corporate-name-drops :no-philosopher-name-drops-in-her-voice)

  :rename-note
  "RENAMED 2026-07-13 by architect redirect. Previously staged as
   'book-of-training-4b/'. Alfred clarified: Book of Training is NOT a
   training-pair corpus — it is an ENGINEERING MANUAL describing HOW
   we train Sakura, and Jess is being dispatched separately to write
   that manual. This package is supplement training material for the
   Sakura 4B fold — the SFT-shaped pairs Alfred asked for, still
   valuable, still authored — but it must not be confused with the
   engineering manual. Hence: training-pair-supplements-4b."

  :warning
  "THIS IS NOT A BOOK. This is training data.

   Every record in this package is a supervised-fine-tuning pair (or a
   small bundle of pairs) in :messages chat-training format. The
   assistant-turn text is still publishable prose — kid-readable, no
   training-data smell — but the shape of these files is SFT, not
   chapter. If you came here looking for prose you can sit with, go to
   Book of Words, Book of Reason, Book of Self, or Book of Listening
   instead. Those are books. This is what feeds the model.

   THIS IS ALSO NOT THE BOOK OF TRAINING. The Book of Training is an
   engineering manual describing HOW the training pipeline works —
   authored separately by Jess, for engineers, not for the model.
   Do not conflate the two."

  :purpose
  "This is supplement material for Sakura 4B training — NOT the Book
   of Training. Book of Training is the engineering manual authored
   separately.

   Sakura (the 4B model) needs enough word range to express: stutter,
   whisper, chuckle, taken aback, sly, wry, witty, chipper, somber,
   slow, patient, abrupt, warm, rueful, dry, exhausted, amused,
   quiet-proud. She needs to be able to say things like 'sure... check
   this out' in a low tone, extend a small drama across turns
   Godot-shape, express uncertainty with rising intonation, split a
   five-option decision into top-two-with-or, or final-one-upswing.

   This package supplies that range in SFT-shaped pairs, alongside
   three research-backed additions the corpus was thin on:
   objects-in-relation, imagination-vs-reality frame markers, and
   Constitutional-shape critique-revise triples for safety
   dispositions."

  :sections-list
  ((section-A "Objects in their web" "~40 concrete named objects, 8-12 pair-shape passages each")
   (section-B "Shop dialogues WITH-speech + WITHOUT-speech" "~100 scenarios in two modality forms")
   (section-C "Emotional range training" "~700 pairs across 18 emotional targets")
   (section-D "Deliberation-visible scenes" "~30 scenes / ~60 pairs; think-out-loud shape")
   (section-E "Imagination-vs-reality frame markers" "~50 scenes / ~100 pairs")
   (section-F "Constitutional-shape critique-revise triples" "~40 triples / ~120 pairs")
   (section-G "Prosody + decision elicitation patterns" "~100 pairs, splitting-5 patterns and hedges")
   (section-H "Two-flowers Godot continuity" "~40 pairs; small drama held across turns"))

  :format
  "Every SLAT file in this package uses one of two shapes:

   1. (pair :messages (...))     — a single SFT pair, wrapped in a
                                    train-shape record. Fields:
                                    :id, :meta (register/emotion/etc),
                                    :messages ((role user) (content \"...\"))
                                                ((role assistant) (content \"...\"))

   2. (bundle :pairs (...))     — a bundle of related pairs sharing
                                    context. Each :pair inside has its
                                    own :id and :messages.

   The :meta field carries tags the fold script can group on:
     :register  (low / neutral / warm / abrupt / etc.)
     :emotion   (stutter / whisper / chuckle / rueful / etc.)
     :section   (A / B / C / D / E / F / G / H)
     :cite      (paper family: LIMA / Phi / TinyStories / ATOMIC /
                 Character-LLM / Constitutional / RAG / STORIUM / ReAct
                 / GYAFC / EmpatheticDialogues / etc.)
     :shape     (walkthrough / critique-revise / two-turn / decision-split /
                 hedge / godot / deliberation / frame-mark / etc.)

   No markdown. No prose sections. Every record is a training input."

  :not-for
  "Do not put this in front of a human reader expecting a book. Do not
   render it to HTML or EPUB. The manifest lists total pair counts and
   the fold script picks it up as-is."

  :relationship-to-other-books
  "Book of Words teaches the vocabulary of objects.
   Book of Listening teaches the shape of small pairs.
   Book of Self teaches who she is.
   Book of Persona teaches how she holds voice under pressure.
   Book of Reason teaches the seven-lens weave.
   Book of Motion / Music / Games teach the domain material.
   Book of Training (authored separately by Jess) is an engineering
   manual describing HOW Sakura 4B is trained — pipeline, fold, eval,
   audit — for engineers, not for the model.

   Training-Pair Supplements 4B is the SFT-shaped supplement layer
   THAT WRAPS the books for the fold. If a scene from Book of Words
   needs an SFT-shape pair, and it didn't naturally have one, it lives
   here. If a doctrine memory needs a critique-revise triple to teach
   the disposition, that triple lives here. If Alfred wants Sakura to
   say 'sure... check this out' in a low tone, THE PAIR THAT TEACHES
   THAT LIVES HERE."

  :closing
  "Kid at the other end. Publishable prose in the assistant turn. Delicacy under everything.")
